<p style=3D"color: #333;">For most of us, the pandemic is a source of addit=
ional financial stress. I say =E2=80=9Cadditional=E2=80=9D because Gen X is=
 used to being known as savings slackers, maybe due to our unique position =
of supporting both growing children and aging parents. That means worries a=
bout our family=E2=80=99s physical health are compounded by financial healt=
h concerns.</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">Then again, the Great Pause has also put the brak=
es on normal spending patterns. We=E2=80=99re more focused on what=E2=80=99=
s essential, and less able or interested in shopping for fun and sport.</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">This naturally compels us to become more aware of=
 our finances =E2=80=94 which makes it the perfect time to harness the powe=
r of a Japanese technique for mindful budgeting: kakeibo.</p>

<h4 style=3D"font-family: calluna, Georgia, serif; color: #111; font-size: =
22px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 30px;">Kondo your financial house</h4=
>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">Kakeibo (or kakebo) was created by Japanese journ=
alist Hani Motoko in 1904 as a household accounting system, and it blends t=
houghtful goal-setting with bookkeeping. The <a href=3D"https://t.dripemail=
2.com/c/eyJhY2NvdW50X2lkIjoiNDMxMTg3MCIsImRlbGl2ZXJ5X2lkIjoidzRoZTlvMWQzMjM=
