In0" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #be8100;=
">results go beyond</a> simply sticking to a budget and saving.</p>

<blockquote style=3D"background-color: #fafafa; color: #666; font-style: it=
alic; margin-left: 0; padding: 20px 30px;">
<p style=3D"color: #333;">The Japanese believe that tidiness in one=E2=80=
=99s finances is as important as tidiness in one=E2=80=99s house =E2=80=94 =
and indeed for them, the act of thinking mindfully about where one=E2=80=99=
s money goes is in itself a recipe for calm and well-being.</p>
</blockquote>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">To get started, all you need is to know is how mu=
ch money you have available and typically spend, plus a savings goal, and a=
reas you=E2=80=99d like to improve. You=E2=80=99ll also need a pen and pape=
r because this is a handwritten, visual practice.</p>

<h4 style=3D"font-family: calluna, Georgia, serif; color: #111; font-size: =
22px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-top: 30px;">How to use kakeibo</h4>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">At the beginning of the month, you=E2=80=99ll fig=
ure out your budget by subtracting your fixed expenses (rent, food, transpo=
rtation, medical, phone) from your income. You=E2=80=99ll also set a saving=
s goal. Currently, this might seem impossible, but even a small amount does=
 the trick.</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">Kakeibo has you put your expenditures in four buc=
kets: needs (fixed expenses), leisure or wants (what you desire but isn=E2=
=80=99t necessary, like ordering in or purchasing trendy clothes), culture =
(buying books), and extras (unanticipated expenses or one-offs, like birthd=
ay gifts).</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">Each day, jot down what you spend in your ledger.=
 Do this with pen and paper, in real-time. This gives you a chance to slow =
down to become conscious of your habits in the present and consider how it =
may affect your future.</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">At the end of the month, you=E2=80=99ll do a revi=
ew of what you spent, by bucket. Not only will you see the big picture of w=
hether you stuck to your budget and managed to save, but you=E2=80=99ll als=
o notice your successes and your challenges.</p>

<p style=3D"color: #333;">Cultivating awareness helps relieve your worry an=
d fear around money. Ultimately that=E2=80=99s the point of kakeibo: bringi=
ng balance and peace of mind into your day-to-day life. And that in its own=
 right is, well, like money in the bank.</p>

